Package oogasalad.editor.model.data.object.sprite

Class SpriteData

java.lang.Object
oogasalad.editor.model.data.object.sprite.SpriteData
public class SpriteData extends Object
Encapsulates sprite data for an editor object. This class stores sprite properties such as position, frame data, animations, and the path to the sprite's image file. It provides methods to access and modify these properties including frame and animation management.
Author:
Jacob You

    • SpriteData

      public SpriteData(String name, int x, int y, double rotation, Map<String,FrameData> frames, Map<String,AnimationData> animations, String spritePath)
      Constructs a new SpriteData instance with the specified properties.
      Parameters:
      name - the unique name of the sprite
      x - the x-coordinate of the sprite's position
      y - the y-coordinate of the sprite's position
      rotation - the rotation of the sprite
      frames - a map of frame names to their corresponding FrameData
      animations - a map of animation names to their corresponding AnimationData
      spritePath - the file path to the sprite image
